      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong>,<strong> trimmed green beans</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>reserved lemongrass</strong> <strong>outer layers</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the greens to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray and put it in the oven for 10-12 min or until the beans are tender – these are your <strong>soy</strong> <strong>greens</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 parcels!</p>",
