      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
